  "title": "Senior / Operations Executive",
  "description": "<ul><li>Liaising and networking with a range of stakeholders including customers, colleagues, suppliers and their organizations.</li><li>Allocate jobs among material handling workers to efficiently manage material segregation & support hands on as needed.</li><li>Acting as a contact between company and its existing & potential markets. Researching organizations and individuals to identify new leads and potential new markets.</li><li>Negotiating on price, costs, delivery and specifications with buyers and their organization.</li><li>Research upcoming market trend & prepare team for successful execution.</li><li>Perform competitor analysis & strategize with key stakeholders to position the organization ahead of competition.</li><li>Checking the quantities of goods in stock. Preparing reports and sales displays.</li><li>Training personnel and helping team members develop their skill.</li><li>Candidate must possess a Bachelor's degree or above.</li><li>Class 3 Driving License & Fork lift license will be an added advantage.</li><li>Candidate with reasonable english fluency (spoken english) will be considered.</li><li>At least 2 Year(s) of working experience in similar capacity in metal scrap / metal trading industry.</li><li>6 day a week, Monday to Saturday; Timing 8.30am until finish.</li></ul>",
